  "acceptTermsRequired": "You must accept the terms of use and the privacy policy to create an account.",
  "legalCguContent": "Last updated: [to be completed]\n\n1. Purpose\nEchango Promo is a mobile app allowing merchants in a pilot neighborhood (Djelfa) to publish temporary promotions, freely browsable by nearby customers.\n\n2. Merchant registration\nBy creating an account, you certify that the information provided (name, address, category, phone number) is accurate. The PIN code you choose is personal and confidential — Echango Promo never knows it in cleartext.\n\n3. Published content\nYou are solely responsible for the promotions you publish (price, description, photo). Displayed prices must reflect an actual discount. Any misleading, expired-but-not-removed, or fraudulent promotion may be hidden after being reported and reviewed by a moderator (field agent or administrator), without prior notice.\n\n4. Reporting and moderation\nCustomers can report a promotion. Beyond a threshold of distinct reports, the promotion is placed in a moderation queue. A moderator may hide it, validate it, or warn the merchant (the promotion then reverts to draft, requiring an explicit republish).\n\n5. Account suspension\nIn case of clearly fraudulent or repeated content despite a warning, the administrator may suspend a merchant account. The merchant may delete their own account at any time from the app.\n\n6. Limitation of liability\nEchango Promo is a technical intermediary. Echango Promo is not a party to transactions between merchants and customers and does not guarantee the accuracy or actual availability of published promotions.\n\n7. Changes to these terms\nThese terms may evolve, in particular when the app opens to a wider audience. Any substantial change will be announced within the app.\n\n8. Contact\nFor any question regarding these terms: [to be completed — contact email].",
  "legalPrivacyContent": "Last updated: [to be completed]\n\n1. Data collected\nMerchant (account): phone number, business name, address, category, business photo (optional), GPS location (optional), PIN code (never stored in cleartext, only in hashed form).\n\nCustomer: no personal data or account required. An anonymous technical identifier is generated on the device to limit abuse (one report or favorite per device), with no link to a real identity.\n\n2. Purpose\nThis data is used solely for the service to function: displaying promotions and merchant listings, anti-fraud on reports, anonymous usage statistics (view counts).\n\n3. Retention\nPhotos are removed from storage after 30 days of inactivity on the associated promotion; account data (name, phone, history) is kept as long as the account is active. When an account is deleted, data is deactivated immediately (no longer publicly visible) and kept for internal history purposes only, with no further processing.\n\n4. Sharing\nNo data is sold or shared with third parties for commercial purposes. Merchant information (name, address, photo) is public by nature (merchant listing visible to customers).\n\n5. Your rights\nYou can view, correct, or delete your account at any time from the app. For any other request (access, full deletion of historical data): [to be completed — contact email].\n\n6. Security\nPasswords and PIN codes are stored in hashed form, never in cleartext. Administrator and agent access is protected by authentication and restricted by role."
